[2] Brazil (Mato Grosso)
Date: Wed 2 Sep 2009
Source: Jornal Circuito Mato Grosso [in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY,
edited] <http://www.circuitomt.com.br/home/materia/29594>


In the new bulletin addressing the dengue cases in Mato Grosso,
released the Wednesday morning (2 Sep [2009]) by the state
Secretariat of Health (SES/MT), the coordinator of Health
Surveillance of the State Secretariat of Health noted that there were
36 339 dengue cases recorded in the state from January to the present
[date], of which 1095 were recorded as being serious cases of the
disease. With relation to the number of deaths caused by dengue
[virus infection], 34 were recorded with 28 [of these] now confirmed
and 6 still under investigation.

Just in Cuiba, 10 841 dengue cases were registered, of which 420 are
serious cases. Of the 420 serious cases, 322 were confirmed and 98
are under investigation. Of the deaths registered in Cuiba, 8 were
confirmed as being serious cases of the disease and 5 are under
investigation. Currently in Vareza, 3825 cases were reported. Of
these, 440 were reported as being serious cases of the disease, with
274 confirmed and 166 under investigation.

In relation to the same period in 2008, in 2009 Mato Grosso had an
increase of 248 percent of notified dengue cases. Between [1 Jan and
2 Sep 2008], 10 453 dengue cases were registered.

[Byline: Viviane Petroli]

