[5] Sri Lanka
Date: Tue 1 Sep 2009
Source: People's Daily Online, Xinhua News Agency report [edited]
<http://english.people.com.cn/90001/90782/90880/6745602.html>


The number of dengue cases has risen to 24 857 while 245 people have
died of the disease in Sri Lanka so far, the Epidemiological Unit of
the Health Ministry said on Tuesday [1 Sep 2009].

The Epidemiological Unit said in its latest statistics that of the 24
857 cases, the highest number of patients were reported in June
[2009] totaling 7048. It is followed by July [2009]with 6872 cases
being reported.

--
